# API Examples (FastAPI Gemini Service)
#
# Base URL (local):
#   http://127.0.0.1:8000
#
# Auth:
#   Use Bearer token for protected endpoints.
#   Swagger UI: click "Authorize" and paste "Bearer <token>".

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
AUTH
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

1) Register
POST /auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

Request:
{
  "email": "user@example.com",
  "password": "StrongP@ssw0rd"
}

Response:
{
  "id": 1,
  "email": "user@example.com",
  "created_at": "2026-02-04T12:00:00.000Z"
}

curl:
curl -X POST http://127.0.0.1:8000/auth/register \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"email":"user@example.com","password":"StrongP@ssw0rd"}'

2) Login (OAuth2 form)
POST /auth/login
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

Request:
username=user@example.com&password=StrongP@ssw0rd

Response:
{
  "access_token": "<JWT>",
  "token_type": "bearer",
  "expires_in": 86400
}

curl:
curl -X POST http://127.0.0.1:8000/auth/login \
  -H "Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded" \
  -d "username=user@example.com&password=StrongP@ssw0rd"

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
GEMINI (requires Bearer token)
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

1) Send prompt
POST /gemini/requests
Authorization: Bearer <JWT>
Content-Type: application/json

Request:
{
  "prompt": "Hi Gemini!",
  "model_version": "gemini-3-flash-preview"
}

Response:
{
  "id": 1,
  "request_id": "c4a1b9a8-6d5b-4f1a-8b9c-28a2c8c8b9a1",
  "prompt": "Hi Gemini!",
  "model_version": "gemini-3-flash-preview",
  "response": "Hello!",
  "created_at": "2026-02-04T12:00:00.000Z",
  "updated_at": "2026-02-04T12:00:00.000Z"
}

curl:
curl -X POST http://127.0.0.1:8000/gemini/requests \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer <JWT>" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"prompt":"Hi Gemini!","model_version":"gemini-3-flash-preview"}'

2) My history
GET /gemini/requests?limit=50&offset=0
Authorization: Bearer <JWT>

Response:
{
  "total": 1,
  "limit": 50,
  "offset": 0,
  "items": [
    {
      "id": 1,
      "request_id": "c4a1b9a8-6d5b-4f1a-8b9c-28a2c8c8b9a1",
      "prompt": "Hi Gemini!",
      "response": "Hello!",
      "model_version": "gemini-3-flash-preview",
      "created_at": "2026-02-04T12:00:00.000Z",
      "updated_at": "2026-02-04T12:00:00.000Z"
    }
  ]
}

curl:
curl -X GET "http://127.0.0.1:8000/gemini/requests?limit=50&offset=0" \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer <JWT>"

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
ADMIN (requires admin token)
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

1) List users
GET /admin/users?limit=50&offset=0
Authorization: Bearer <ADMIN_JWT>

curl:
curl -X GET "http://127.0.0.1:8000/admin/users?limit=50&offset=0" \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer <ADMIN_JWT>"

2) Get user by id
GET /admin/users/{user_id}
Authorization: Bearer <ADMIN_JWT>

curl:
curl -X GET "http://127.0.0.1:8000/admin/users/1" \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer <ADMIN_JWT>"

3) Update user access
PATCH /admin/users/{user_id}/access
Authorization: Bearer <ADMIN_JWT>
Content-Type: application/json

Request:
{
  "is_active": true,
  "is_admin": false
}

curl:
curl -X PATCH "http://127.0.0.1:8000/admin/users/1/access" \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer <ADMIN_JWT>" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"is_active":true,"is_admin":false}'

4) List all Gemini requests
GET /admin/gemini/requests?limit=50&offset=0&user_id=1
Authorization: Bearer <ADMIN_JWT>

curl:
curl -X GET "http://127.0.0.1:8000/admin/gemini/requests?limit=50&offset=0&user_id=1" \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer <ADMIN_JWT>"
